01: RESEARCH is a dataset-backed research CLI. You use it to:
02: - Get datasets in, inspect their schema, run analyses, and save results and artifacts (tables, charts, docs).
03: - Drive work with hypotheses, producing clear outputs you can revisit.
04: 
05: Start here:
06: 1) Sign in
07: - research login
08: 
09: 2) See what you already have
10: - research datasets ls            # remote datasets you can use
11: - research local ls               # local files RESEARCH can import
12: 
13: 3) If you have a local file to use next
14: - research import "/absolute/path/to/file.csv" --name my_dataset --mode auto
15: Then:
16: - research describe my_dataset
17: - research query my_dataset "Show 10 example rows and basic field stats."
18: 
19: 4) If you want to explore an existing dataset
20: - research describe <dataset_name>
21: - research query <dataset_name> "Top 20 records by <metric> with fields <a,b,c>."
22: 
23: 5) If you have a hypothesis to test
24: - research plan <dataset_name> "Hypothesis: …"
25: - research run <dataset_name> --prompt "Test the hypothesis; subset=<…>; metrics=<…>; charts=<type, x, y>."
26: 
27: When you need data that isn’t in any dataset yet, create a research environment and pull in public sources and your files:
28: - research env create --dataset my_project --name "Baseline" --prompt "Acquire sources A,B; normalize to tables X,Y; validate Z; produce a dataset brief."

